message.content:
One of the most significant events that happened in São Tomé and Príncipe in the past 100 years is the end of Portuguese colonial rule and the subsequent independence of the country. 

On July 12, 1975, São Tomé and Príncipe officially gained independence from Portugal, marking a major milestone in the country's history. This event paved the way for self-governance and the establishment of a democratic government. It also ended nearly five centuries of Portuguese colonial rule in the islands.

The independence of São Tomé and Príncipe brought about political and social changes, as the country transitioned to a new era of self-determination. This event allowed the people of São Tomé and Príncipe to shape their own destiny and embark on a path of development and nation-building.
